<div class="callout">
  <h2 style="margin-top:0;">If macros are blocked when you open the file</h2>
  <p>Since 2022, Microsoft blocks macros by default in any Office file downloaded from the internet. You'll see a red banner reading <em>"BLOCKED — Macros from the internet are blocked"</em> with no enable button. This is a generic Microsoft default and is not specific to FISCO.</p>
  <p>To unblock the file:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Close the file in Excel if it's open.</li>
    <li>In Windows Explorer, right-click the downloaded <code>.xlsm</code> file → <strong>Properties</strong>.</li>
    <li>At the bottom of the <strong>General</strong> tab, find the <strong>Security</strong> section and tick <strong>Unblock</strong>.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>OK</strong>, then re-open the file. Macros will now run normally.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>If your organisation's IT policy still blocks macros after unblocking, ask your IT team to add the file's folder as an Excel <strong>Trusted Location</strong>. We are working on digitally signing the macros, which will allow IT to permit them via a trusted-publisher policy across your organisation.</p>
</div>

<h2>Using a test scenario</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Download the country model (or your own copy of the template).</li>
  <li>Download a scenario file from the same country.</li>
  <li>Open the model in Excel, with macros enabled.</li>
  <li>Run the Import Plan macro and point it at the scenario file. The scenario inputs will populate the relevant cells, leaving the rest of the model untouched.</li>
  <li>Inspect the assessment outputs to see how that scenario fares against the rule.</li>
</ol>

<h2>System requirements</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Microsoft Excel 2019 or later (Windows or Mac).</li>
  <li>Macros enabled (required for the Eurostat data fetcher and the Import Plan macro).</li>
  <li>Internet connection for live Eurostat updates.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Mac compatibility</h2>
<p>An Excel-for-Mac entry point is provided via the <code>EurostatUpdateMac</code> macro. Some elements of the workflow are still Windows-first; full parity is in progress.</p>

